FBIS4-40273 "drsov116bb_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Calls IAEA Resolution `Start of Sanctions' Calls IAEA Resolution `Start of Sanctions' SK1606111894 Moscow Radio Moscow in Korean 1100 GMT 16 Jun 94 SK1606111894 Moscow Radio Moscow Korean BFN [Text] Son Song-pil, DPRK ambassador in Moscow, has said that the Korean [choson] Government withdrew from the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] because this agency's Board of Governors had recently adopted a resolution on the North Korean issue. During a news conference, Ambassador Son Song-pil stressed that the IAEA Board of Governors' adoption of the resolution meant, in reality, the start of sanctions against the DPRK. Ambassador Son Song-pil also declared that imposing sanctions against Pyongyang and convening an international conference on the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula were in no way compatible.
